answers.answer: Could be a sign of pre eclampsia.

they've said that but I've only had a high blood pressure twice& just went today&is fine. my dad has high blood pressure but sometimes when he's tested is not high.  I don't know but I just want to know

What do you want to know? Other than it a sign of preclampsia, don't mean it is for sure. But your dr doesn't seem to be all that concerned. You're already 35 wks anyway if you did have it, your baby is most likely healthy enough for delivery. It's a risk to you not so much baby.

I had protein in my urine near the end of my last pregnancy that was not preeclampsia-related. I had GD and was controlling my blood sugar with diet, but the protein in my urine was a sign that I was not eating enough and so my body was consuming itself, in a way. I ended up going into labor @ 36 weeks because of this.
I didn't state whether my doctor is concerned or not. that's not my point. I'm simply asking what other doctors had said to other mothers.

question: I have high levels of protein in my urine @ 35 weeks. anyone else?  what has your doctor told you about it?
title: protein in urine
